--- !u!114 &331369471
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 331369469}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 5f7201a12d95ffc409449d95f23cf332, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  m_Material: {fileID: 0}
  m_Color: {r: 0.19607843, g: 0.19607843, b: 0.19607843, a: 1}
  m_RaycastTarget: 1
  m_Maskable: 1
  m_OnCullStateChanged:
    m_PersistentCalls:
      m_Calls: []
  m_FontData:
    m_Font: {fileID: 12800000, guid: e1f6029887635d841a95cbfb7666b1b8, type: 3}
    m_FontSize: 30
    m_FontStyle: 0
    m_BestFit: 0
    m_MinSize: 3
    m_MaxSize: 50
    m_Alignment: 0
    m_AlignByGeometry: 0
    m_RichText: 1
    m_HorizontalOverflow: 0
    m_VerticalOverflow: 0
    m_LineSpacing: 1
  m_Text: "Welcome to Net Zero.\n\nNet Zero is a resource management game where you
    will be in charge of creating power plants in order to create an energy grid.
    Your main objective in Net Zero is to achieve net zero carbon emissions by the
    year 2050. \n\nNet Zero will start you off in the year 2020 and have you go through
    the four seasons of the year after which you will jump to the year 2035 and then
    to the final year of 2050.\r\n\nBy playing through Net Zero you will see the
    drastic choices humanity may have to make in the near future in order to get
    our carbon output to a net zero and also see the financial costs that it will
    take to achieve this goal. \r\n\nBy the end, you should have gained a greater
    understanding of how much we will have to change and spend in order to save our
    planet.\r\n\nHow To Play:\r\nYour primary tool that will be used to play Net
    Zero will be either your mouse or your finger depending on if you are playing
    on PC or Mobile. Your keyboard is not going to be needed when playing Net Zero.\r\n\nYou
    will be able to zoom in and out of the map of Net Zero by using the scroll wheel
    on your mouse or on mobile you can use the scroll bar seen on the side of the
    screen.\r\n\nIn Net Zero you will start out in the year 2020 with a few power
    plants already built for you. Your first goal will be to build the power plants
    that you want in order to meet the Power Consumption. You will do this by clicking/tapping
    on an empty grid tile which will then bring up a build menu. In this build menu
    you will see all of your build options as well as what makes each power plant
    different. You will have to compare the variables of cost, energy produced, and
    carbon produced. Maintaining balance between these variables is the key to having
    a successful run in Net Zero.\r\n\nIn Net Zero you will have the ability to turn
    your power plants on and off. Doing this will help save on carbon output. You
    can do this by clicking/tapping on the power plants. When a plant is turned off
    it will have a red outline to indicate this. By keeping the proper amount of
    plants running to maintain the energy being consumed and turning off the plants
    that aren't needed to meet that consumption is a balance will be key to success.\r\n\nIn
    the fall of 2020 the Power Consumed is going to gradually start increasing and
    it will continue to do so every time the seasons change from this point on in
    the game.\r\n\nIn the winter of 2020 you will be given your first policy. These
    are decisions that you will have to make in order to lower the carbon output.
    The correct choice will lower the carbon more than the incorrect so choose carefully.\r\n\nWhen
    you reach 2035 you will now have the ability to destroy power plants that you
    have previously built. You can destroy the plants by clicking/tapping on the
    Power Plants the same way you did to turn them on and off.\r\n\nTechnical Support:\r\nShould
    a bug appear while you are playing Net Zero do not panic it should be a simple
    fix. What we suggest you do is refresh the website and try playing it again.
    If this does not work we suggest you contact the development team who will try
    and resolve your issue as quickly as possible so you can get back into the fun.\r\n\nIn
    your message please provide the following:\r\nThe bug that is appearing\r\nThe
    events leading up to this bug\r\nAny other information you think will be useful
    in helping resolve your issue\r\nIf through discord @ the DevTeam so they see
    the message\r\n\nThe team can be contacted in through these different resources:\r\nEmail:
    netzerodevs@gmail.com\r\nDiscord: https://discord.gg/XEdVAg\r\n"
